f serialization within the JVM, particularly in a native environment where direct references might be elusive. I’m considering whether the agent's configuration for serialization needs to capture specific data. However, it seems we might lack serialization metadata due to an incomplete test scenario. Also, I’m pondering if the Native Image serialization situation necessitates avoiding class name mutations. If the condition isn't met for the base class during deserialization, registration may not occur. There’s definitely a lot to unpack here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_m4t0PKEZoW63oouX0Y2WKkhR|fc_0b4ac0637a5e4add016a3fa7d6ce9481969605e284fb843d6a", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/ProvEdDSAPublicKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n", "newText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void serializationRoundTripRestoresPublicKeyReturnedByBasePrivateKey() throws Exception {\n        EdDSAPrivateKey basePrivateKey = privateKeySerializedAsBaseClass();\n        PublicKey basePublicKey = assertInstanceOf(PublicKey.class, basePrivateKey.getPublicKey());\n\n        assertEquals(PROVIDER_PUBLIC_KEY_CLASS_NAME, basePublicKey.getClass().getName());\n        assertEquals(\"Ed25519\", basePublicKey.getAlgorithm());\n\n        assertSerializationRoundTrip(basePublicKey);\n    }\n\n    private static void assertSerializationRoundTrip(PublicKey basePublicKey) throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void serializationRoundTripRestoresPublicKeyReturnedByBasePrivateKey() throws Exception {\n        EdDSAPrivateKey basePrivateKey = privateKeySerializedAsBaseClass();\n        PublicKey basePublicKey = assertInstanceOf(PublicKey.class, basePrivateKey.getPublicKey());\n\n        assertEquals(PROVIDER_PUBLIC_KEY_CLASS